  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed basement flat constitutes a sub-standard form of accommodation by virtue of poor outlook and undue sense of enclosure for a family unit and the internal layout of the scheme fails to consider appropriate vertical stacking to reduce noise and vibration impacts. The development fails to demonstrate that the second floor flat would achieve a floor to ceiling height over 2.5m for at least 75% of the GIA and the development fails to provide easy and inclusive access to the communal garden to meet the needs of different occupiers. As such the development would provide a substandard living environment for future occupiers contrary to Development Management Policies DMD 5, DMD 9, London Plan policies D5 and D6, the London Plan Housing SPG, the LP Housing Design Standards 2023, the Technical housing standards - NDSS 2015, and the NPPF 2024.",
    "The proposed development includes a mix of dwelling types and sizes that fail to reflect  the most up to date evidence as set out in the Councils Local Housing Needs Assessment (2020) and, in doing so, compromises the quality of unit sizes for which there is the greatest need. As such the development is considered unacceptable and contrary to Core Strategy Policy C5, London Plan policy H3, Draft Local Plan policy H3 and the London Borough of Enfield Council Local Housing Need Assessment 2020 LNHA Final Report dated November 2020 and the NPPF 2024.",
    "Insufficient details have been provided within the submitted Flood Risk Assessment and SUDs Strategy Report to ensure appropriate flood mitigation measures are in place and that surface water run-off is managed as close to its source as possible. As such the proposals fail to comply with DMD Policies 59, 60, 61 62, CP Policy C21 and 28 and London Plan policy SI 12 and SI 13 and Draft Local Plan policy SE7."
  ],
